Karabo Moekoena's burnt body was found in Lyndhurst last month after she was reported missing. JOHANNESBURG - The family and friends of Karabo Mokoena, a 22-year-old woman murdered allegedly by her boyfriend, will on Wednesday remember her at a memorial service in Diepkloof, Soweto. Karabo Mokoena's burnt body was found in Lyndhurst last month after she was reported missing.Her boyfriend, Sandile Mantsoe, was arrest for her death last week.Mokoena s uncle, Tshepo Mokoena, says the family is still not coming to terms with the loss. It s very hard there are moments where we re not sure whether she s gone or still around especially because we fetched her body from the mortuary. I had to rush my brother to the doctor because he could not take it. WATCH: Karabo's uncle: We are traumatised(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)